  "key_observations_html": "<aside class=\"crypto-story-callout\" aria-labelledby=\"key-obs-callout-title\"><p class=\"crypto-story-callout__title\" role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"3\" id=\"key-obs-callout-title\">Key observations</p><ul class=\"crypto-story-callout__list\"><li><strong>TMMF distributed value rose 2.7% over 30D:</strong> With distributed value at $13.29B (2.7% higher over 30D), more institutional cash appears to be parking in tokenized MMFs\u2014supporting the view that TMMFs are being used as operational liquidity, not just a niche yield experiment. That keeps TMMFs relevant as institutional settlement and treasury infrastructure, not only a short-term yield sleeve.</li><li><strong>TMMFs are becoming a de facto settlement layer for institutions:</strong> Against a firmer distributed value print (2.7% over 30D), several of the largest funds combine very high AUM with small holder counts\u2014e.g. USYC (47 holders, $3.01B; ~$64M/holder), iBENJI (34 holders, $1.63B; ~$48M/holder), BUIDL (113 holders, $2.86B; ~$25M/holder)\u2014suggesting on-chain cash and collateral rails rather than broad retail savings products. Ethereum still carries ~47% of aggregated MMF network share, alongside selective deployment on chains used for institutional workflows.</li><li><strong>Multi-chain deployments still look more like distribution requirements than deep liquidity:</strong> Multi-chain deployment headlines often reflect compliance and distribution requirements rather than deep liquidity on every chain\u2014compare with funds that list many networks but very few holders. <a href=\"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMitAFBVV95cUxNZ2VXN0UzQm9pRjRMT2NHaGx0X3hUcV92THg2NVB0QmZ3NWJGeGRvam1iQlMtU1Q0RG9UUTRPa0VRT0FCTm5QbUZrb29qRHdGLUgxRlFTR1NzdHNydEN4OVFTN2NyaEI4enpsdmV0TURCY0VRTzBBSGZVdVNiY05xRGhOMmFFS3RvMmgzTnE2TC1VSVFVMmdIUGhOaGRVeWdnZVk3bDA4SHJkaGdPVHI5Q3RSTUo?oc=5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WisdomTree expands tokenized fund access to Solana in multichain push - CoinDesk</a> (Google News); <a href=\"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMirwFBVV95cUxOWUNWY2cyMEFCellqTWxaTklhS01aSzJEQnBuY3hRM2htSUdvd0FFTXBNSDVnMVRlRmx4SEp6VUR6R0ZJMUpHbktLZ1dEajZab3d4V0VMbVl0YUpqTWJLMW5ub1p0ZmpxSElQcFhvY25Ta2VJdXZRRlFzMUVnSnNfcjJUWTM2RmZ4Wjg2RGtJY3RhejdQYWN1SlJENHYtczhSNHZpLUVZQUYwd0lXX3lJ?oc=5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Apex Group commits to T-REX Ledger for multi-chain tokenized fund distribution - ledgerinsights.com</a> (Google News).</li><li><strong>Issuer strategy coverage is splitting institutional rails from retail yield products:</strong> Issuer strategy coverage can clarify whether the market is bifurcating into institutional rails vs retail yield products\u2014holder counts and AUM per holder in the funds table help validate that split. <a href=\"https://thedefiant.io/converge/tradfi-and-fintech/edx-markets-closes-76m-series-c-led-by-sbi-holdings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">EDX Markets Closes $76M Series C Led by SBI Holdings</a> (The Defiant); <a href=\"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/ethsystems-launches-privacy-tools-for-institutional-ethereum\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">EthSystems Launches Privacy Tools for Institutional Ethereum</a> (The Defiant).</li><li><strong>Settlement and cash-rail stories are reinforcing institutional TMMF use:</strong> Settlement and cash-rail headlines align with funds that combine large AUM with small holder bases\u2014compare with the funds table and whether issuers are positioning products as on-chain liquidity, not retail savings. <a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/07/14/for-pension-funds-tokenization-s-real-play-is-balance-sheet-management-fidelity-s-lai-says\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">For pension funds, tokenization\u2019s real play is balance-sheet management, Fidelity\u2019s Lai says</a> (CoinDesk); <a href=\"https://cointelegraph.com/news/anchorage-digital-expands-tron-support-with-institutional-trx-staking?utm_source=rss_feed&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=rss_partner_inbound\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Anchorage Digital expands Tron support with institutional TRX staking</a> (CoinTelegraph).</li></ul><p class=\"crypto-story-callout__note\">Context only\u2014not investment advice. Observations rank fund-level and network aggregates on this page against recent tokenization and money-market headlines. Bullets are ranked from on-page data and recent industry headlines (dashboard RSS plus Google News fallback).</p></aside><p class=\"review-note ko-disclaimer\">Key observations are AI generated and should be reviewed for accuracy.</p>",
